description: Three connected folios forming a single foldout with circular diagrams

f69v.notes: Full circular diagram with labels around perimeter

f70r1.notes: Circular diagram, some text in non-standard positions (Y, I, X)

f70r2.notes: Circular diagram on left, SEPARATE paragraph text block on far right

oddities.description: Large block of paragraph text separate from circular diagram
oddities.interpretation: Text linguistically resembles Currier A more than AZC diagram text. May be misclassified in transcript as AZC when functionally A-like.

user_observations: All 3 folios appear to be the same foldout
Text on far right of f70r2 is visually separate from diagrams
Separate text does NOT look like circular diagram text
Separate text looks more like Currier A paragraph text
